703866f-a.title: Brooklyn: Cozine Avenue - Essex Street
703866f-a.text:
522 Cozine Ave., (east and west across the front of the two buildings),
south side, between Essex Street (right), and Shepherd Ave. (left).
The barn is on the line of the southeast corner of Essex Street and Cozine
Ave., and will, eventually, be either moved or demolished. This view shows
also an extensive view of one of the few remaining farms in Eings County.
Wortman Ave. is roughly laid out in the foreground.
July 5, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
